---
description: Core project context for the apartment management system
alwaysApply: true
---
- This is an apartment/society management system. Real residents will use this
  for logins, complaints, and maintenance payments — treat financial and
  personal data (payment refs, contact info, vehicle info) as sensitive.
- Stack: React (client/), Express (server/), Neon Postgres (server/src/db).
- Roles: resident, tenant, manager, admin, association_staff, treasurer.
  Every protected route must check role, not just "logged in."
- Never invent npm packages. Before importing something new, verify it's
  installed (check package.json / run npm list) rather than assuming.
- No placeholder code. If a function can't be fully implemented, say why
  and stop — don't leave "// TODO" in committed code.
- Before any multi-file change, propose a short plan first (Plan Mode) —
  don't jump straight to editing across the codebase.